WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.360
e, Chris, abbiamo creato un clima di Pontignano dentro la Commissione europea,

00:06.980 --> 00:09.080
che è abbastanza un raggiungimento.

00:09.300 --> 00:14.000
Allora, cercherò di rispondere alla vostra questione, Chris,

00:14.860 --> 00:21.860
non referendo quasi a tutto al campo in cui ho cercato di essere attivo,

00:21.940 --> 00:24.320
ma cercherò di rispondere in termini più generali.

00:25.220 --> 00:27.880
Allora, se guardiamo i ultimi 10 anni,

00:28.640 --> 00:36.240
l'Europa, che è spesso trattata di non aver messo in posto sufficienti reformi strutturali,

00:36.460 --> 00:37.880
e possiamo tutti sbagliare su questo,

00:38.660 --> 00:43.620
ha messo in posto 4 strutturali strutturali storiche di se stessa.

00:44.220 --> 00:46.660
È molto conosciuto che, solo in 10 anni,

00:46.920 --> 00:49.960
ci sia stato l'accedimento del mercato singolo,

00:50.160 --> 00:54.080
del mercato singolo, dell'enlargimento e della Costituzione.

00:54.080 --> 00:58.840
Questo è molto conosciuto, ma è troppo facilmente dimenticato.

00:59.180 --> 01:02.760
E non dovremmo dimenticare che ogni esercizio di questi obiettivi

01:02.760 --> 01:06.500
è stato pronunciato come quasi impossibile

01:06.500 --> 01:09.940
da molto dell'intelligenza in Europa,

01:10.260 --> 01:12.000
negli Stati Uniti e altrimenti,

01:12.180 --> 01:14.220
forse un o due anni prima,

01:14.400 --> 01:18.940
che è passato in posto punctuale.

01:18.940 --> 01:24.960
Ora, credo che sia anche normalmente sbagliato

01:24.960 --> 01:27.300
quanto queste 4 cose

01:27.480 --> 01:32.640
possano avere una relazione con il grande problema dell'economia europea

01:32.640 --> 01:34.540
e la sua competitività.

01:34.880 --> 01:37.960
E' in più di nessun dubbio che l'Europa non presta bene

01:37.960 --> 01:40.320
dal punto di vista della competitività,

01:40.480 --> 01:43.660
ma vorrei fare il punto che,

01:43.660 --> 01:46.800
è che questo possa essere in parte a causa

01:46.800 --> 01:49.500
della concentrazione delle energie politiche

01:49.500 --> 01:52.660
su questi 4 obiettivi,

01:53.620 --> 01:55.740
ma che, allo stesso tempo,

01:55.920 --> 01:59.540
avendo trasformato l'Europa in questo modo,

01:59.760 --> 02:00.180
per esempio,

02:00.580 --> 02:04.660
rendendo l'Europa un po' più simile all'U.S. come un'entità,

02:04.820 --> 02:08.480
può solo aiutare la crescita futuro e la competitività in Europa.

02:09.640 --> 02:11.140
È chiaro, per esempio,

02:11.140 --> 02:14.120
che la singola correnza

02:14.120 --> 02:15.700
ha portato con la correnza

02:18.780 --> 02:22.060
da indisciplina fiscale a disciplina fiscale.

02:22.420 --> 02:24.620
È ben possibile che, nel termine sottile,

02:24.760 --> 02:27.240
questo possa aver portato una crescita più bassa,

02:28.160 --> 02:29.620
ma credo che tutti aggrediremmo

02:29.620 --> 02:33.820
che questo sia un prequisito sottile per il sviluppo futuro.

02:34.960 --> 02:37.060
Anche la costituzione,

02:37.060 --> 02:40.360
solo il mercato, solo la correnza, l'enlargimento,

02:40.400 --> 02:42.060
la costituzione, anche la costituzione.

02:42.840 --> 02:44.560
Giuliano, che è la relazione

02:44.560 --> 02:47.560
tra la costituzione e la competitività?

02:47.600 --> 02:48.520
Non c'è una relazione.

02:50.280 --> 02:52.440
Ma è chiaro a tutti

02:52.440 --> 02:56.220
che una compagnia non può essere competitiva

02:56.220 --> 02:59.500
se ha un processo di decisione veloce e incerta.

03:01.260 --> 03:03.920
Questo non è molto diverso per la nostra nazione

03:03.920 --> 03:05.580
o per un set di nazioni.

03:05.580 --> 03:09.220
A livello che la costituzione

03:09.220 --> 03:11.840
porti un processo di decisione

03:11.840 --> 03:13.460
più racionali e veloci,

03:15.480 --> 03:19.480
credo che questo aiuterà la competitività d'Europa.

03:20.120 --> 03:22.580
Quindi, quando vedremo

03:23.120 --> 03:27.140
i ultimi 10 anni della storia europea,

03:27.680 --> 03:30.660
credo che confermerà che l'Europa

03:30.660 --> 03:33.680
non ha fatto abbastanza bene

03:33.680 --> 03:35.780
dal punto di vista della performance economica,

03:36.700 --> 03:39.220
ma probabilmente abbastanza la base

03:39.220 --> 03:42.080
per una performance economica più soddisfatto

03:42.080 --> 03:44.060
dal punto di vista dell'Europa.

03:45.120 --> 03:46.900
È chiaro, però,

03:47.260 --> 03:49.920
che non possiamo solo restare là

03:49.920 --> 03:51.940
e aspettare questa struttura fondamentale

03:51.940 --> 03:54.360
di trasformazione per portare a livello

03:54.360 --> 03:56.580
la dividenza in termini di crescita più alta

03:56.580 --> 03:59.100
e dell'implicamento e della competitività.

03:59.100 --> 04:02.340
Ci sono le politiche necessarie.

04:03.180 --> 04:04.480
E qui, Chris,

04:05.520 --> 04:06.860
per rispondere alla vostra domanda

04:06.860 --> 04:08.700
o al titolo di questa sessione,

04:08.840 --> 04:10.580
i successi e i setbacki in Europa

04:10.580 --> 04:11.720
over the past 10 years,

04:12.020 --> 04:14.700
what I would regard as a major problem

04:14.700 --> 04:16.980
which has emerged more and more clearly

04:16.980 --> 04:19.520
is a decoupling.

04:19.620 --> 04:22.440
A decoupling by member state

04:22.440 --> 04:24.000
between two things.

04:24.740 --> 04:27.380
The willingness to accept

04:27.380 --> 04:30.680
a somewhat greater integration and coordination

04:30.680 --> 04:32.540
Europe-wise,

04:33.000 --> 04:36.760
selectively, without exceeding,

04:36.860 --> 04:39.160
with greater attention paid at the same time

04:39.160 --> 04:40.580
also to subsidiarity,

04:40.920 --> 04:43.240
but to accept some greater coordination

04:43.240 --> 04:46.180
in certain area, one prerequisite,

04:46.260 --> 04:49.020
and the other one to be serious and tough

04:49.020 --> 04:51.480
in terms of domestic economic reforms.

04:52.340 --> 04:55.000
To simplify things exceedingly,

04:55.000 --> 04:57.660
I believe that we have seen

04:57.660 --> 04:59.760
an increasing decoupling in Europe

04:59.760 --> 05:02.460
between these two necessary prerequisites,

05:02.460 --> 05:03.160
in my view,

05:03.620 --> 05:06.020
in order to have a competitive Europe,

05:06.220 --> 05:09.160
not just an internal competition

05:09.160 --> 05:10.540
between one and the other.

05:11.060 --> 05:12.160
To simplify things,

05:12.680 --> 05:14.920
and at the risk of being unjust,

05:15.680 --> 05:18.180
certainly Germany and France

05:18.180 --> 05:20.380
have once again displayed

05:20.380 --> 05:23.240
a greater willingness to accept coordination,

05:23.240 --> 05:26.180
including in the constitutional debate,

05:27.660 --> 05:29.740
than, say, the UK or Spain.

05:30.140 --> 05:31.700
At the same time, there have been

05:31.700 --> 05:33.460
pretty recalcitrant in terms of

05:33.460 --> 05:34.880
domestic economic reforms.

05:35.600 --> 05:37.540
I believe we need both things

05:37.540 --> 05:39.220
if we want a competitive Europe,

05:39.340 --> 05:41.400
but there has been this increasingly

05:41.400 --> 05:42.680
visible decoupling.

05:43.260 --> 05:45.300
Now, I think we should ask ourselves

05:45.300 --> 05:48.220
the question, is there an inherent conflict

05:48.220 --> 05:50.180
between these two attitudes,

05:50.700 --> 05:51.860
both of which, in my view,

05:51.860 --> 05:53.800
are necessary for a competitive Europe?

05:54.260 --> 05:56.960
I believe there is not inherent conflict.

05:57.780 --> 05:59.440
Of course, as I said,

06:00.020 --> 06:01.280
a great deal of attention,

06:01.400 --> 06:03.960
and here we can only learn from the UK,

06:04.440 --> 06:05.880
has to be paid to subsidiarity.

06:07.060 --> 06:08.300
And in certain areas,

06:08.540 --> 06:10.500
we have in the last ten years

06:10.500 --> 06:12.860
brought about greater coordination,

06:13.900 --> 06:17.160
but some devolution to the national authorities.

06:17.520 --> 06:19.120
I can here mention perhaps

06:19.120 --> 06:20.720
the reform in the area of competition.

06:20.720 --> 06:22.740
But I don't see that

06:22.740 --> 06:24.200
there is an inherent conflict

06:24.200 --> 06:25.800
between these two attitudes.

06:26.280 --> 06:28.040
And I must say, Italy, for one,

06:28.140 --> 06:29.420
as I see it,

06:30.320 --> 06:32.680
has been rather more close

06:32.680 --> 06:33.880
to Germany and France

06:33.880 --> 06:35.240
in terms of acceptance

06:35.240 --> 06:37.220
of a greater degree of coordination,

06:37.700 --> 06:39.140
and, at least in principle,

06:39.320 --> 06:41.860
but also with some implementations

06:41.860 --> 06:45.340
ready towards economic reforms domestically.

06:45.680 --> 06:47.000
Now, in this context,

06:47.000 --> 06:49.900
I see a very substantial hope

06:49.900 --> 06:52.280
in the enlargement.

06:52.480 --> 06:53.600
We normally consider

06:53.600 --> 06:55.780
the effects of enlargement

06:55.780 --> 06:57.820
at constant policies.

06:58.260 --> 06:59.540
Enlargement will not

06:59.540 --> 07:01.360
keep policies constant.

07:01.620 --> 07:03.300
Enlargement will transform

07:03.920 --> 07:05.980
the policy trade-offs, I believe.

07:06.560 --> 07:07.600
And what I see

07:07.600 --> 07:08.780
in the new member states,

07:08.840 --> 07:10.280
most of them, all of them,

07:10.600 --> 07:12.520
is at the same time the willingness

07:12.520 --> 07:14.040
to have greater coordination

07:14.040 --> 07:15.980
and, for sure, a strong

07:15.980 --> 07:18.180
central enforcer of the rule

07:18.180 --> 07:19.260
of the European Commission

07:19.900 --> 07:21.920
and a tough policy of domestic

07:21.920 --> 07:22.940
economic reform.

07:23.680 --> 07:25.960
And here, again, to make one

07:25.960 --> 07:27.460
reference to Italy,

07:28.500 --> 07:29.600
with all the abstraction

07:29.600 --> 07:31.580
of these geometrical discussions

07:31.580 --> 07:33.140
about foreign politics,

07:33.780 --> 07:36.020
I believe that a country like Italy,

07:36.420 --> 07:38.020
with a government like the present

07:38.020 --> 07:39.020
government of Italy,

07:39.640 --> 07:41.520
should perhaps even intensify

07:41.520 --> 07:43.900
the efforts to become a reference point

07:43.900 --> 07:45.680
without discarding

07:45.680 --> 07:47.820
other friendships and alliances

07:47.820 --> 07:49.920
for this group

07:49.920 --> 07:51.760
of small

07:51.760 --> 07:53.720
and or new

07:53.720 --> 07:55.720
member states, which are really

07:55.720 --> 07:58.600
rejuvenating the European Union.

08:02.380 --> 08:04.060
My time is almost over.

08:05.320 --> 08:05.800
One

08:07.340 --> 08:07.820
important

08:09.240 --> 08:09.720
setback

08:09.720 --> 08:11.900
or insufficient progress

08:11.900 --> 08:13.720
is the explanation

08:13.720 --> 08:15.940
of Europe to Europe's citizens,

08:17.080 --> 08:17.800
in particular

08:17.800 --> 08:19.240
to the younger generations.

08:20.160 --> 08:21.780
And here I see,

08:21.780 --> 08:24.020
frankly, a monumental paradox.

08:24.600 --> 08:25.000
Why?

08:25.580 --> 08:27.440
We all know that the younger generations

08:27.440 --> 08:29.920
lose interest and love

08:29.920 --> 08:31.660
for Europe, especially because

08:31.660 --> 08:33.920
they have not lived through the things

08:33.920 --> 08:36.100
that Europe has been able to remove.

08:37.220 --> 08:38.220
And at the same

08:38.220 --> 08:40.300
time, if we think of it, Europe

08:40.300 --> 08:42.260
is the key ally

08:42.260 --> 08:44.400
of the future generations.

08:44.740 --> 08:46.340
Giuliano referred to

08:46.340 --> 08:48.460
the dimension of the future, as I

08:48.460 --> 08:49.320
see it.

08:50.480 --> 08:52.520
Europe is the main driver,

08:52.780 --> 08:54.300
the main introducer

08:54.300 --> 08:56.140
of a reference to the future

08:56.140 --> 08:58.440
in our societies and in our debates,

08:58.960 --> 09:00.380
both in terms of

09:00.380 --> 09:02.320
forcing us all to consider

09:02.320 --> 09:04.480
the future and in terms

09:05.280 --> 09:06.260
of forcing

09:06.260 --> 09:07.980
us to respect the future,

09:08.200 --> 09:10.300
consider the future. What would have

09:10.300 --> 09:12.740
been in each of our countries

09:12.740 --> 09:14.440
the policies, the

09:14.440 --> 09:16.440
politics, if we had not

09:16.440 --> 09:18.340
had the target of 1993

09:18.860 --> 09:20.040
for the single market,

09:20.560 --> 09:22.540
of 1997, to bring down

09:22.540 --> 09:23.140
the deficit?

09:24.260 --> 09:26.280
Now Lisbon is a bit weak because it

09:26.280 --> 09:28.560
does not crucify

09:28.560 --> 09:30.140
countries similarly

09:30.140 --> 09:31.540
effectively to that.

09:32.100 --> 09:34.260
So if there has been a reference to the

09:34.260 --> 09:36.380
future, it has been most of the times

09:36.380 --> 09:38.460
brought by what the collective

09:38.460 --> 09:40.460
wisdom of member states and the commission

09:40.460 --> 09:42.680
have decided

09:42.680 --> 09:44.220
should be a future

09:44.220 --> 09:45.620
reference for Europe.

09:46.220 --> 09:48.000
And it has forced

09:48.000 --> 09:50.220
countries and societies to

09:50.220 --> 09:51.400
respect the future.

09:52.900 --> 09:53.700
And really,

09:54.520 --> 09:55.860
many of our countries

09:55.860 --> 09:58.400
were running with

09:58.400 --> 10:00.200
a beatitude of

10:00.200 --> 10:02.340
unawareness, deficits of

10:02.340 --> 10:04.220
12-15% of GDP

10:04.220 --> 10:06.300
without there being any debate.

10:07.080 --> 10:08.360
This was so at the beginning

10:08.360 --> 10:10.040
of the last ten years, Chris.

10:10.420 --> 10:12.340
Now we make

10:13.440 --> 10:14.200
fights

10:14.200 --> 10:16.540
about whether it is 2.9

10:16.540 --> 10:17.680
or 3.1.

10:18.060 --> 10:20.400
But the substantial effect of

10:20.400 --> 10:22.660
Europe is that it has forced

10:22.660 --> 10:24.260
upon domestic political

10:24.260 --> 10:26.560
processes the respect for our

10:26.560 --> 10:28.340
children, for the future

10:28.340 --> 10:30.460
generations, not to have

10:30.460 --> 10:32.540
them born with the burden

10:32.540 --> 10:35.200
on their shoulders of the public debt.

10:35.600 --> 10:36.540
So I think

10:36.540 --> 10:38.500
that it should be possible, and

10:38.500 --> 10:40.600
I'm delighted that President Barroso

10:40.600 --> 10:42.600
has assigned a special responsibility

10:42.600 --> 10:44.440
to Vice President Marco

10:44.440 --> 10:46.540
Wallstrom to make an effort to

10:46.540 --> 10:48.780
explain Europe. I think that those

10:48.780 --> 10:50.540
to whom we find

10:50.540 --> 10:52.600
it most difficult to transfer

10:52.600 --> 10:54.440
the message of Europe, that is

10:54.440 --> 10:56.740
the younger generations, are really those

10:56.740 --> 10:58.440
which we should be able to

10:58.440 --> 11:00.420
mobilize. Final note,

11:01.240 --> 11:02.380
I think in ten years

11:02.380 --> 11:04.720
the relevance of the commission

11:04.720 --> 11:06.100
for all its weaknesses

11:07.480 --> 11:08.880
has increased.

11:09.380 --> 11:10.720
May I conclude with

11:10.720 --> 11:11.820
a personal

11:12.440 --> 11:14.500
reference here. Ten years

11:14.500 --> 11:15.960
ago, believe it or not,

11:16.360 --> 11:18.680
when I was first appointed to Brussels,

11:19.840 --> 11:20.860
Italian journalists,

11:21.780 --> 11:22.840
non-Italian journalists,

11:22.980 --> 11:24.600
were totally uninterested in

11:24.600 --> 11:25.420
my person.

11:25.420 --> 11:28.220
It genuinely asked me

11:28.220 --> 11:29.660
the question, but Professor,

11:29.780 --> 11:31.780
why on Earth, on Earth

11:31.780 --> 11:33.420
have you accepted to become

11:33.420 --> 11:34.340
European Commission?

11:35.400 --> 11:37.360
Well, last July

11:37.360 --> 11:39.720
I had at least the great satisfaction

11:39.720 --> 11:41.800
that nobody asked

11:41.800 --> 11:43.400
me, in Italy or elsewhere,

11:44.060 --> 11:45.460
Professor, why do you appear

11:45.460 --> 11:47.520
not entirely happy of not being

11:47.520 --> 11:49.060
able to continue to work

11:49.740 --> 11:51.540
at the core of the European

11:51.540 --> 11:53.140
process? Thank you, Chris.

11:59.140 --> 12:02.260
The Council of Côme, intent on

12:02.260 --> 12:03.920
burying German sovereignty,

12:04.100 --> 12:06.160
there was Monsieur Mitterrand,

12:06.400 --> 12:07.580
there was Jacques Delors,

12:08.940 --> 12:10.160
and that they had a vision of

12:10.160 --> 12:12.100
Europe and they were able to

12:12.100 --> 12:13.280
explain it to people and they

12:13.280 --> 12:14.980
were able to infuse people.

12:15.780 --> 12:17.760
And that today the

12:17.760 --> 12:19.540
generation of political leaders

12:19.540 --> 12:21.960
have no vision,

12:22.780 --> 12:23.900
all have

12:23.900 --> 12:25.400
an existential problem

12:25.400 --> 12:27.400
with countries

12:28.200 --> 12:29.860
membership of the European Union.

12:30.740 --> 12:32.340
I wonder if you think

12:32.340 --> 12:34.220
that is true

12:34.220 --> 12:36.020
and I'd be very interested

12:36.020 --> 12:38.080
in your reflections on the other

12:38.080 --> 12:39.280
issue as well.

12:39.740 --> 12:41.080
Mario, would you like to start?

12:45.080 --> 12:47.700
I think we should try to create

12:47.700 --> 12:49.880
enthusiasm through concrete

12:49.880 --> 12:50.760
facts.

12:53.160 --> 12:55.060
And I believe that

12:55.060 --> 12:56.340
both your questions, Chris,

12:56.380 --> 12:57.240
are linked.

12:58.100 --> 12:59.760
Can I start from the last one?

13:00.080 --> 13:02.160
Conventional narrative about Europe.

13:03.120 --> 13:04.380
I think that Mitterrand

13:04.380 --> 13:05.920
called Delors era

13:05.920 --> 13:07.260
was a great one.

13:08.500 --> 13:09.900
But I think

13:09.900 --> 13:12.180
it was largely responsible

13:12.180 --> 13:14.640
for some of the subsequently

13:14.640 --> 13:15.900
intervened problems.

13:17.220 --> 13:18.160
Many of the things

13:18.160 --> 13:20.200
that Neil has done

13:20.200 --> 13:22.880
and talked about this evening

13:23.980 --> 13:24.370
are

13:24.760 --> 13:26.200
related remedies

13:27.260 --> 13:28.740
to an excess

13:28.740 --> 13:30.320
of vision relative

13:30.320 --> 13:31.280
to administration.

13:34.020 --> 13:36.360
And this has contributed

13:36.360 --> 13:38.550
to impoverishing the vision

13:38.720 --> 13:40.340
about Europe in our

13:40.340 --> 13:40.880
citizens.

13:42.080 --> 13:44.260
So I spoke earlier of a decoupling.

13:44.700 --> 13:46.420
I think here there is another decoupling.

13:46.560 --> 13:48.640
I think we should try to bring

13:48.640 --> 13:51.460
vision and administration hand in hand.

13:51.600 --> 13:52.860
Maybe I'm too pragmatic.

13:53.000 --> 13:55.260
Maybe I'm too British. I'm sorry for that.

13:56.560 --> 13:56.980
But, you know,

13:57.020 --> 13:58.840
having been in charge of the single market

13:58.840 --> 14:00.580
first and competition, then

14:00.580 --> 14:02.140
how can one avoid

14:02.940 --> 14:04.040
these influences?

14:09.060 --> 14:10.560
And this links

14:10.560 --> 14:12.360
back to the issue of explanation.

14:12.960 --> 14:14.880
When will we be able to

14:14.880 --> 14:16.900
bring to European citizens the notion

14:16.900 --> 14:19.100
that the commission

14:19.100 --> 14:21.250
employs a staff which is

14:21.580 --> 14:23.080
smaller than the

14:23.080 --> 14:24.680
city of Rotterdam does?

14:25.680 --> 14:27.160
And one third of it

14:27.160 --> 14:28.940
is related to translations

14:28.940 --> 14:30.040
and interpretations.

14:30.740 --> 14:32.660
So I think there is

14:32.660 --> 14:34.300
a closer

14:34.870 --> 14:36.840
link between vision and

14:36.840 --> 14:38.980
administration than we

14:38.980 --> 14:41.200
normally see. As to your first

14:41.200 --> 14:42.980
question, is there or not

14:42.980 --> 14:45.090
still an ideological divide?

14:45.090 --> 14:47.270
Well, here I have

14:47.270 --> 14:49.050
a personal, very strong

14:49.050 --> 14:51.230
conviction. I think it's

14:51.230 --> 14:52.690
profoundly wrong

14:52.690 --> 14:55.330
to reason in the following way.

14:56.550 --> 14:57.410
Low turn-out

14:57.410 --> 14:59.190
rates to the European elections,

14:59.550 --> 15:00.490
which is a fact.

15:01.450 --> 15:03.190
Hence there is a

15:03.190 --> 15:05.190
crisis in the politics

15:05.190 --> 15:07.070
of Europe. Hence

15:07.070 --> 15:09.450
let's try to make the politics

15:09.450 --> 15:11.130
of Europe as similar as

15:11.130 --> 15:12.810
possible to national politics.

15:12.810 --> 15:15.110
In my view,

15:15.550 --> 15:17.050
the crisis is a much wider

15:17.050 --> 15:19.070
one of the political

15:19.070 --> 15:20.910
process and of the democratic

15:20.910 --> 15:22.730
process of

15:22.730 --> 15:24.690
participation to the elections

15:24.690 --> 15:26.890
at the national level as well

15:26.890 --> 15:28.210
as the European level.

15:28.790 --> 15:30.770
And I'm glad that the

15:30.770 --> 15:32.970
Constitution did not go as far

15:32.970 --> 15:34.810
as many would have liked it

15:35.330 --> 15:36.870
to go in terms of

15:36.870 --> 15:38.930
mimicking the play of

15:38.930 --> 15:40.030
domestic politics.

15:40.770 --> 15:42.310
I think that

15:44.410 --> 15:46.310
the European Commission

15:46.310 --> 15:47.270
of course

15:47.270 --> 15:49.150
should have a president

15:49.150 --> 15:51.670
politically connotated

15:51.670 --> 15:53.410
with some involvement

15:53.410 --> 15:54.770
of the European Parliament

15:54.770 --> 15:56.430
in the selection of the president,

15:56.930 --> 15:59.150
but I think

15:59.150 --> 16:00.310
it would be the end

16:00.310 --> 16:01.850
of the European construction

16:01.850 --> 16:04.310
if we had, as many

16:04.310 --> 16:06.550
would like to see, a commission

16:06.550 --> 16:08.350
that is an executive, which is

16:08.350 --> 16:10.390
a centre left one or a centre

16:10.390 --> 16:12.490
right one. Can you just

16:12.490 --> 16:14.330
imagine what the reaction

16:14.330 --> 16:16.370
in the different member states, depending

16:16.370 --> 16:18.710
on their current political majorities,

16:18.930 --> 16:20.650
would be to decisions of enforcing

16:20.650 --> 16:22.430
the law in that member state if

16:22.430 --> 16:24.410
the colour of the commission is different from

16:24.410 --> 16:25.650
the one of the member state?

16:30.090 --> 16:32.410
So, I think it would be a

16:32.410 --> 16:33.810
profound mistake.

16:34.870 --> 16:36.490
Does this mean that

16:36.490 --> 16:38.990
the European Commission is not a political body?

16:39.470 --> 16:40.350
No, in my view.

16:40.750 --> 16:42.590
But in a sense, it is

16:42.590 --> 16:44.270
the party of integration,

16:44.890 --> 16:46.890
which can have more

16:46.890 --> 16:48.680
right-wing, more left-wing connotations.

16:49.590 --> 16:50.510
I think it's

16:50.510 --> 16:52.610
very important to have had

16:52.610 --> 16:54.370
an input. I mean,

16:54.490 --> 16:56.490
I think one of the problems of

16:59.550 --> 17:00.250
some

17:00.250 --> 17:02.630
rights in our member

17:02.630 --> 17:03.970
states recently

17:03.970 --> 17:05.630
arriving to power

17:05.630 --> 17:08.210
is the erroneous belief that

17:08.210 --> 17:10.370
because there was

17:10.370 --> 17:11.590
a predominantly

17:11.590 --> 17:14.430
majority of the left in the European

17:14.430 --> 17:16.190
Council in a previous

17:16.190 --> 17:18.210
age, then the European Union

17:18.210 --> 17:19.670
is a product of the left.

17:20.350 --> 17:22.430
I think that much of the European Union

17:22.430 --> 17:23.970
is a product of

17:25.210 --> 17:26.230
conservative thinking.

17:27.330 --> 17:27.990
The single

17:27.990 --> 17:30.030
market is largely the product of

17:30.030 --> 17:32.010
Mr. Thatcher. The single

17:32.010 --> 17:33.850
currency is largely

17:34.630 --> 17:35.770
the product,

17:35.870 --> 17:37.710
political speaking, Chancellor Call.

17:39.310 --> 17:40.290
And I

17:40.290 --> 17:41.970
love it when

17:41.970 --> 17:43.830
I see in the Commission

17:43.830 --> 17:45.890
that we have

17:45.890 --> 17:48.170
different positions not

17:48.170 --> 17:50.270
based on affinity

17:50.270 --> 17:51.990
to this or that political family.

17:52.290 --> 17:53.910
But if anything, or

17:53.910 --> 17:56.210
flag, if anything, more linked

17:56.210 --> 17:58.190
to the portfolio for which

17:58.190 --> 18:00.250
we are responsible, which is

18:00.250 --> 18:01.950
a logical, a rational

18:01.950 --> 18:04.070
assignment of responsibility.

18:04.710 --> 18:06.490
So I'm sure I did not

18:06.490 --> 18:08.050
answer to your question.

18:08.170 --> 18:10.370
Maybe I used enthusiasm after

18:10.370 --> 18:12.610
having said that we should drop it.

18:13.110 --> 18:14.290
But in terms of

18:16.130 --> 18:18.590
ideological divide and the political

18:18.590 --> 18:20.330
play at the European Union

18:20.330 --> 18:22.370
level, I firmly believe

18:22.370 --> 18:24.510
that the biggest mistake would

18:24.510 --> 18:26.250
be to

18:27.910 --> 18:28.430
just to try

18:28.430 --> 18:30.730
to make it identical to the domestic level.

18:30.890 --> 18:32.670
And of course here too explanation

18:32.670 --> 18:34.610
is important. The commissioners

18:34.950 --> 18:36.570
are faceless Eurocrats.

18:37.650 --> 18:38.670
Of course we are faceless.

18:39.410 --> 18:40.750
Of course we are Eurocrats.

18:41.270 --> 18:42.890
But we lack

18:42.890 --> 18:43.510
legitimacy.

18:45.650 --> 18:46.550
Mention to me

18:46.550 --> 18:48.630
one national government in

18:48.630 --> 18:50.190
Europe, not the US,

18:51.330 --> 18:52.690
where ministers,

18:52.790 --> 18:54.030
if I can for a second,

18:54.870 --> 18:56.870
presumptuously assimilate commissioners

18:56.870 --> 18:58.830
to ministers,

18:59.670 --> 19:00.750
undergo an individual

19:00.750 --> 19:02.770
written and oral scrutiny

19:02.770 --> 19:04.950
by the parliament. Of course

19:04.950 --> 19:07.090
one can say that there has

19:07.090 --> 19:09.190
been before

19:09.190 --> 19:10.930
that a parliamentary

19:10.930 --> 19:12.870
election, but we know this is not

19:12.870 --> 19:14.170
the case for all ministers.

19:15.330 --> 19:16.870
And at any rate they were not

19:16.870 --> 19:18.210
elected to be ministers.

19:18.910 --> 19:20.850
They have not gone through this individual

19:20.850 --> 19:21.410
scrutiny.

19:22.690 --> 19:24.770
This is again one myth

19:24.770 --> 19:27.230
that obviously we have not been able

19:27.230 --> 19:28.610
to dispel.

19:29.210 --> 19:30.890
And it's ludicrous to see

19:30.890 --> 19:32.970
people still convinced that the European

19:32.970 --> 19:35.030
parliament lacks any

19:35.030 --> 19:36.970
power when on the 15th

19:36.970 --> 19:39.310
of March, the edes of March

19:39.310 --> 19:40.630
of 1999,

19:42.350 --> 19:42.470
Neil,

19:43.110 --> 19:44.850
myself and other

19:45.590 --> 19:46.870
18 colleagues

19:46.870 --> 19:48.610
went back home

19:48.610 --> 19:50.910
at midnight as

19:50.910 --> 19:52.970
resigned commissioners. By the way

19:52.970 --> 19:55.170
I was very much impressed

19:55.170 --> 19:56.930
that that evening

19:56.930 --> 19:59.110
for the first time I saw a

19:59.110 --> 20:00.210
30 minutes cover.

20:01.590 --> 20:03.250
Thanks. Thank you.

20:04.070 --> 20:04.750
Mario.

20:04.830 --> 20:06.590
I thought the question was to Neil.

20:08.930 --> 20:09.310
Mario,

20:09.650 --> 20:10.890
you will give the same answer

20:10.890 --> 20:12.630
in a 30 minutes.

20:15.930 --> 20:17.290
Perfect substitutability.

20:18.950 --> 20:19.410
Well,

20:19.570 --> 20:20.350
Minister Baldassari,

20:20.350 --> 20:22.690
the European model

20:22.690 --> 20:24.470
is for one generation.

20:25.170 --> 20:26.690
My view is that

20:27.150 --> 20:28.550
the inertial

20:28.550 --> 20:30.390
European model, the

20:30.390 --> 20:32.450
de facto configuration in most

20:32.450 --> 20:34.870
of our member states, would be

20:34.870 --> 20:36.050
for one generation.

20:36.510 --> 20:38.230
The premium to the present relative

20:38.230 --> 20:40.350
to the future. It is the effort

20:40.350 --> 20:42.770
of the European Union to persuade

20:42.770 --> 20:44.370
member states

20:44.370 --> 20:46.290
to modify their

20:46.290 --> 20:48.470
de facto model into one

20:48.470 --> 20:50.550
which pays more attention to the future.

20:51.470 --> 20:51.770
And

20:52.470 --> 20:54.790
in this abstract

20:54.790 --> 20:56.710
and so pleasant

20:56.710 --> 20:58.170
academic environment

20:58.170 --> 21:00.670
in which we find ourselves this evening

21:00.670 --> 21:02.910
of course the future

21:02.910 --> 21:04.570
does bring us to the notion

21:04.570 --> 21:05.470
of investment

21:06.450 --> 21:09.030
and therefore to the metal

21:09.030 --> 21:10.990
which you reminded

21:10.990 --> 21:12.650
linking that metal

21:12.650 --> 21:14.250
to a rule

21:14.250 --> 21:16.330
have not mentioned

21:16.330 --> 21:17.810
that rule now.

21:18.470 --> 21:20.470
There is no question that in economic

21:20.470 --> 21:22.570
terms you know this

21:22.570 --> 21:24.110
better than anybody else.

21:25.190 --> 21:26.650
What is public

21:26.650 --> 21:28.390
or private expenditure

21:28.390 --> 21:31.030
for the future is more worthwhile

21:31.030 --> 21:32.730
than what is public

21:32.730 --> 21:34.510
or private consumption.

21:34.950 --> 21:36.650
But as you said yourself

21:38.030 --> 21:40.450
it's difficult then to identify

21:40.450 --> 21:42.810
what precisely is investment.

21:43.350 --> 21:44.550
And I was

21:44.550 --> 21:46.850
struck by a comment of our colleague

21:47.090 --> 21:49.150
Joachim Ammunia at a recent

21:49.150 --> 21:50.750
seminar in Italy

21:50.750 --> 21:52.750
where six members

21:52.750 --> 21:54.730
of the Italian government were present

21:54.730 --> 21:56.910
and Ammunia afterwards

21:56.910 --> 21:58.750
noted that each of the

21:58.750 --> 22:00.710
minister had excellent

22:00.710 --> 22:02.550
reasons to say

22:02.550 --> 22:04.550
that his

22:05.570 --> 22:06.290
expenditure

22:06.290 --> 22:08.370
I was going to say his or her

22:08.370 --> 22:10.790
but minister Moratti was not there on this occasion

22:10.790 --> 22:12.770
but probably with

22:12.770 --> 22:14.170
very good justification

22:14.510 --> 22:16.190
she would say the same.

22:18.150 --> 22:19.110
So that's why

22:19.110 --> 22:20.550
but so

22:20.550 --> 22:23.170
just a reference

22:23.170 --> 22:24.710
to the debate

22:24.710 --> 22:27.070
Neil and I and others had when

22:27.070 --> 22:29.030
the stability pact was created

22:29.030 --> 22:30.970
my position in the commission

22:31.330 --> 22:32.870
in 1997 was

22:32.870 --> 22:34.730
that we should pay attention

22:34.730 --> 22:36.870
to this distinction but we

22:36.870 --> 22:39.150
should also rush up to establish

22:39.150 --> 22:41.050
the methodology, the verification

22:41.050 --> 22:42.390
to assess

22:42.990 --> 22:44.570
what is what.

22:49.930 --> 22:50.830
Very last question.

22:52.650 --> 22:53.030
Perhaps

22:53.030 --> 22:54.390
you can be quite brief.

22:56.150 --> 22:56.690
Very short.

22:57.790 --> 22:59.050
Mario Monti

22:59.050 --> 23:00.030
said that

